  <h2>Agent Architecture</h2>
  <p>The agent uses the <strong>ReAct (Reasoning + Acting)</strong> pattern: the LLM alternates between reasoning about the current state and selecting a tool to call. Each tool result is fed back as an observation, and the loop continues until the LLM determines the recon objective is met.</p>
  <pre><code># ReAct agent loop (pseudocode):
#
# while not done:
#   thought = llm.think(system_prompt, history, current_objective)
#   action  = llm.choose_tool(available_tools, thought)
#   if action == "finish":
#       report = llm.generate_report(history)
#       break
#   observation = tools[action.name](**action.args)
#   history.append(thought, action, observation)
#
# Key design decisions:
# - Max iterations: 20-30 (prevent infinite loops)
# - Context window management: summarize old history when approaching limit
# - Tool timeout: 30s per tool call (LDAP queries can be slow)
# - Error handling: tool failure → LLM decides to retry or skip</code></pre>

